  "title": "Architectural Project Manager (Intermediate)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure design complies with all statutory requirements</li>\n  <li>Managing design development of the project</li>\n  <li>Execute tender procurement</li>\n  <li>On-site construction supervision</li>\n  <li>Procure statutory compliance for TOP and CSC</li>\n  <li>Monitor the making good of defects and final certification</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>A degree in Architectural, Civil/ Structural/ Electrical/ Mechanical Engineering, Building Science or Quantity Surveying.</li>\n  <li>The degree shall be recognised either by the respective professional bodies, professional institutions or BCA</li>\n  <li>A minimum of seven (7) years of practical experience in Project Management Services (for intermediate position)</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Public Sector Standard Conditions of Contract for Construction Work</li>\n  <li>Attended and passed the \"Construction Safety Course for Project Managers” conducted by agencies approved by the Ministry of Manpower.</li>\n  <li>The PM shall work with the Architect and the Consultants in the planning, co-ordination, reporting and implementation of the Project.</li>\n</ol>",
